Belgium to Cut Budget Deficit to 2.8% in 2012, Standaard Reports

-- B y   A n d r e w   C l a p h a m
-- 
2011-04-13T06:17:12Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-13/belgium-to-cut-budget-deficit-to-2-8-in-2012-standaard-reports.html
Belgium ’s caretaker government
plans to cut the budget deficit to 2.8 percent of gross domestic
product in 2012, Prime Minister Yves Leterme told the European
Central Bank yesterday, De Standaard reported.  The government also plans to reduce the nation’s debt to
88.4 percent of GDP by 2015, according to the newspaper. The
debt ratio may even fall below 84 percent should the government
“valorize financial stakes,” the newspaper said, citing a
statement from the premier.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew Clapham at 
 aclapham@bloomberg.net  